  <activityInformation><![CDATA[<p>Great Value Travel passes Purchase a travel pass and only pay one inclusive price for your trips. Lake Constance ‘Seebären’ regional pass (pre-bookable) £59, 3 days £76, 7 days This excellent value ‘all-inclusive’ regional pass is recommended for guests staying in Constance, Lochau and Bregenz. With unlimited FREE travel on the fleet of passenger boats, as well as FREE entrance to many of the regions attractions, it is the perfect way to get to know the area! Free unlimited travel on the ‘White Fleet’ passenger boats around the lake including to Constance, Lindau, Bregenz, Meersburg, Mainau, Friedrichshafen, Stein am Rhein, Überlingen and Schaffhausen for the Rhine Falls Free entrance to 170 attractions in the region including Friedrichshafen Zeppelin museum, Meersburg castles, Salem castle, Unteruhldingen ‘Village on Stilts’ and Sea Life Konstanz Free travel on Pfänder cable-car near Bregenz, and Säntis cable-car in Switzerland Free entrance to many village, art and culture museum Subject to change. Travel on catamaran and car ferry services not included. Things to do in Lochau ‘Bregenzer Festspiele’ opera takes place in nearby Bregenz on the lake stage mid July – mid August Pfänder cable-car near Bregenz for hill walking, museum, falconry shows and panoramic views of the lake (10 mins by train) Good local bus service and excellent railway links to surrounding area Regular performances by the famous ‘Lindau Puppet Opera’ with intricate hand-made puppets Several lakeside cafés and restaurants Lindau town festival with live music takes place approx. mid-July Municipal museum in old town with changing art and culture exhibitions Excellent network of cycle paths around the lake</p>]]></activityInformation>
