  <description><![CDATA[<p>The small town of Lochau lies at the edge of Lake Constance in the bay between Bregenz and Lindau which are both just 5 minutes away by train.</p>
<p>Lake Constance is one of the largest freshwater lakes in Europe, covering a total area of approximately 220 square miles. The lake shares its shores with 2 other countries, <a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="/{localLink:7422472e-08b9-4b72-8b8e-d85bf11a9f9d}" target="_blank" title="Switzerland">Switzerland</a> and <a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="/{localLink:201b2330-bda0-4d32-ae9b-a7946ef8523a}" target="_blank" title="Germany">Germany</a>, and enjoys an exceptionally mild climate with palm trees, exotic plants and flowers growing effortlessly.</p>]]></description>
