<p>Lake steamers can take you to attractive spots such as attractive Meersburg, with its old castle and vineyards, the lovely 'Flower Island' of Mainau, with its fabulous gardens, and Lindau, a delightful bustling Bavarian island town. Constance, Germany, the largest town on the lake, has a fascinating history and a beautiful frescoed traffic-free old town with cobbled streets, brimming with shops, cafés, and wine cellars and reached by train or boat from Lindau. The boat landing stage for some excursions is just in front of our hotel, the Seehotel am Kaiserstrand.</p>]]></thingsToDo>
